<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4814551>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 3. Miconia papillopetala Kriebel & Almeda. A. Branch showing stem indument and asymmetric leaf bases. B. Leaf abaxial surface showing symmetric and asymmetric leaf veins. C. Flowering branch. D. Fruiting branch. E. Floral bud with fused sepals terminating in an apiculum. F. Flower at anthesis (petal color lost in ethanol preserved material). G. Longitudinal section of the hypanthium of a flower at anthesis. H. Petal. I. Stamen (profile view). J. Style and stigma. From the holotype." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4814551/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4814565>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 8. Miconia brenesii Standley. A. Indument of a secondary vein on the abaxial foliar surface. B. Detail of the indument on abaxial foliar surface. C. Flower bud with sepals not fused into an apiculum. D. Flower an anthesis. E. Detail of the dorsal and ventral view of the anther thecae. F. Detail of petal adaxial surface showing. G. Profile view of a seed. H. Close up of an angle of a seed. From R. Kriebel 3665 (INB). Scale bar = 100 µm (A–B, F–H), and 500 µm (C–E)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4814565/files/figure.png" .

