        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 7. Miconia brenesii Standl. A. Branch showing mostly glabrous internodes and symmetric and slightly asymmetric leaf bases. B. Leaf abaxial surface showing asymmetric leaf veins. C. Inflorescence. D. Flower. E. Floral bud lacking fused sepals. F. Longitudinal section of flower bud. G. Flower at anthesis. H. Longitudinal section of a flower at anthesis. I. Longitudinal section of a flower at anthesis showing detail of the hypanthium and ovary. J. Petal. K. Stamen lateral view. L. Stamen dorsal view. M. Style and stigma. A–D by Kenji Nishida. E–M. From R. Kriebel 3665 (INB)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4814563/files/figure.png" .

