        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 4. Miconia papillopetala Kriebel & Almeda. A. Flower bud with its fused sepals rupturing apically. B. Flower an anthesis. C. Indument on a secondary vein on the abaxial foliar surface. D. Close up of stamens showing geniculate filaments. E. Detail of petal adaxial surface showing papillae. F. Seed. From the holotype. Scale bar = 500 µm (A–D), and 100 µm (E–F)." ;
